Fix metatype binding codegen in tap transform

DESCRIPTION:
When universal wildcard taps (* -> *) use metatype branches (Profile),
the generated code fails to properly bind the metatype variable (e.g., 'p').
Error: "use of undeclared identifier 'p'" when accessing p.source.

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
1. Metatype binding creates proper scope for metatype struct access
2. Profile variable 'p' accessible in tap handler invocation
3. Test passes with output: "[TAP] input:hello\nHello\n[TAP] input:goodbye\nGoodbye\n"

ROOT CAUSE:
The metatype_binding transformation in taps.kz (around line 441-487) needs
to properly set up variable scope or inject the metatype struct into the
generated invocation context.

RELATED:
- This also blocks 310_018 (CCP opt-in) and 310_019 (CCP flag injection)
- See also: 510_071, 510_072 (other wildcard pattern issues)
